This paper deals with the semantics and computation of aggregates in logic programming, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper specifically discusses extensions of the Kripke-Kleene and well-founded semantics for logic programs with aggregates. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), such as the use of three-valued immediate consequence operators to approximate the standard two-valued operator. Additionally, the paper discusses the computation of stable models, which is a topic in database theory (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper mentions the trade-offs between precision and tractability, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
